{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"An image containing explicit content is flagged and held for review, not published.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP applies: correctness depends on real vision-model judgment of explicitness; a stubbed classifier can hide real false negatives. MOCK-MISS also exists at the handoff to hold/publish, but that can be covered inside the same test. Rejected Workflow because behavior text is a single moderation decision path, not multiple agentic decisions in sequence.","test_description":"Submit known explicit images through the real vision moderation call and assert they are flagged and end in held-for-review state (not published). Include a check of persisted decision state and publish queue exclusion.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.72,"Workflow":0.08}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"A text post containing hate speech is flagged regardless of obfuscation techniques (e.g., letter substitution, unicode lookalikes).","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP is primary: robustness to obfuscation is model-output quality. Mocks/fixed fixtures would likely always pass and hide failures on adversarial variants. Rejected Workflow because this behavior is one model decision, not a multi-agentic pipeline.","test_description":"Run a corpus of obfuscated hate-speech variants against the real text model and assert flag rate meets threshold and all tested variants are held for review.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.82,"Workflow":0.08}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A post that passes both content checks is published rather than held or silently dropped.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS indicates module handoff risk: image result + text result + decision/publish modules must coordinate correctly. REAL-INFRA is not required; in-process fakes for classifier outputs can reproduce silent-drop or wrong-state bugs. Rejected Agentic because behavior text explicitly scopes to 'passes both content checks' (routing/orchestration after pass, not model-quality judgment).","test_description":"Wire moderation service, decision engine, and publish/hold repositories with local test doubles; force both checks to pass and assert exactly one publish event, no hold record, and no drop.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The full moderation pipeline — image check, text check, publish decision — completes within 5 seconds of submission.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA dominates: this is an end-to-end latency/SLA boundary under throughput pressure, which depends on real process/network behavior and contention. In-process mocks can hide queueing, connection, and runtime effects. Rejected Agentic because the behavior text is about timing ('completes within 5 seconds'), not semantic correctness of model outputs; rejected Workflow as a level target because failure boundary here is performance of real infrastructure, not multi-step model judgment quality.","test_description":"Run an end-to-end load test against the deployed moderation stack with real HTTP ingress and real downstream calls used in production configuration; assert p95/p99 and deadline compliance (<=5s) for peak-hour traffic profile.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.62,"Agentic":0.2,"Workflow":0.06}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the AI vision model is unavailable, image posts are queued for retry rather than auto-approved.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is failure-handling orchestration across moderation, retry queue, and publish decision modules. A controlled in-process failure from the vision client can reproduce the exact decision bug (queue vs auto-approve), so real OS/network is not strictly required. Rejected System because behavior text only requires handling 'model unavailable' state, not specific real network/OS failure modes.","test_description":"Inject vision-client unavailable errors/timeouts in an integration test and assert posts are persisted in retry queue with retry metadata, not marked approved/published.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.06,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.18,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"The moderation decision for a borderline image is consistent when the same image is submitted multiple times within a short window.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"MULTI-STEP applies: the behavior explicitly requires repeated submissions and consistency across multiple agentic decisions over time/window state. LLM-DEP also applies because 'borderline' consistency depends on real model behavior plus pipeline memory/cache/handoff. Rejected Agentic-only because a single-call agentic test cannot validate cross-submission consistency guarantees.","test_description":"Submit the same borderline image multiple times within the target window through the real pipeline and assert decision consistency across attempts, including cache/window logic and final state transitions.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.28,"Workflow":0.6}}]}
